Pat @Ranch Steak{10%ounce} dry; season with half the @Bold & Savory Steak Spice{1%tablespoon} and @salt{}.

Drizzle @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot large pan. Add steak; cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Transfer steak to a #plate{}.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

While steak cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard root end from @Baby Lettuce{1}(chopped into bite-size pieces); chord into bite-size pieces. Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Halve @Mini Cucumber{1} lengthwise and thinly slice.

Lightly crush @Croutons{2} in their #bag{}.

In a large #bowl{}, toss chopped lettuce, @Mixed Greens{2%ounce}, tomatoes, cucumber, and croutons with as much @Blue Cheese Dressing{3%ounce} as you like; season with salt and @Pepper{} to taste.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide salad between #bowls{} and top with steak; sprinkle with @Crispy Fried Onions{1} and serve.